Known Zap extension modes at the time of writing...

Name	   Mode Name(s) Author		Description/notes
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
ZapMJE	  C		Martin Ebourne	Modes for viewing files in a
	  C++				number of popular modern programming
	  Java				languages
	  Assembler
	  Pascal
ZapEmail  Email		Darren Salt	Zap's Email mode
ZapBASIC  BASIC		Dominic Symes	Tokenised BASIC editing
	  BASTXT			Detokenised BASIC editing
	  TaskWindow			Task windows
ZapBasAsm BASasm	Carl Hetherington Assembler colouring for BASTXT
ZapHTML			Matthew Hambley Commands (and mode) for HTML
ZapInform		Graham Nelson	Colouring for Inform scripts
ZaSAsm	  SAsm		James Freeman	Mode for SAsm files
Buttons	  Buttons	Tim Tyler	Button bars for Zap
ForZap	  ForZap	Tim Tyler	Colouring for files of Zap commands
HoTMeaL	  HoTMeaL	Tim Tyler	Colouring for HTML files
Messages  Messages	Tim Tyler	Colouring for 'Messages' files.
ZapTeX	  TeX		Tim Tyler	Colouring for TeX and LaTeX files.
ZapPerl	  Perl		Tim Tyler	Colouring for Perl
ZapObey	  Obey		Tim Tyler	Colouring for Obey files
StrongZap Strong	Tim Tyler	Colouring for StrongHelp files
ZapMan	  Man		David O'Shea	Mode for unix Man files.


